<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Vagrant on Atlas</title><link>https://www.javiercd.es/en/tags/vagrant/</link><description>Recent content in Vagrant on Atlas</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 23 Nov 2025 12:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://www.javiercd.es/en/tags/vagrant/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>03 - Manual OpenStack installation guide with Vagrant</title><link>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/03-instalacion-manual-introduccion/03-instalacion-manual-introduccion/</link><pubDate>Sun, 23 Nov 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/03-instalacion-manual-introduccion/03-instalacion-manual-introduccion/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="introduction-and-scope"&gt;Introduction and scope&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this series, I will show you how to manually deploy a minimal OpenStack installation on a lab of virtual machines managed with Vagrant. We&amp;rsquo;ll use Caracal 2024.1, the latest available in Ubuntu&amp;rsquo;s stable repositories. The goal is not to provide a production solution, but to understand the components, key configuration files, and the correct deployment order so that a basic cloud works with Keystone, Glance, Placement, Nova, Neutron, Cinder, and Horizon.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>04 - Environment deployment and preparation</title><link>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/04-despliegue-del-escenario/04-despliegue-del-escenario/</link><pubDate>Sun, 23 Nov 2025 12:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.javiercd.es/en/posts/openstack/curso-openstack/instalacion-manual/04-despliegue-del-escenario/04-despliegue-del-escenario/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;First, we need to bring up our environment. As mentioned in the previous post, clone my &lt;a href="https://github.com/javierasping/openstack-vagrant-ansible#" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;repository&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git clone git@github.com:javierasping/openstack-vagrant-ansible.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;git clone https://github.com/javierasping/openstack-vagrant-ansible.git
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Once cloned, everything related to these posts is in the &lt;code&gt;manual-install&lt;/code&gt; directory, so cd into it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="bring-up-the-machines-with-vagrant"&gt;Bring up the machines with Vagrant&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inside the repository you&amp;rsquo;ll find the Vagrantfile. Simply run:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;vagrant up
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;After launching, make sure the machines are up:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;vagrant status
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;Current machine states:
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;controller01 running &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;libvirt&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;compute01 running &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;libvirt&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;storage01 running &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;libvirt&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;To connect to the VMs, you can use:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>